utils.stacks

Interface Stack<T>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - the generic of elements in the stack
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    ArrayStack, LinkedStack, VectorStack

    public interface Stack<T>
    The Interface Stack represents a last-in-first-out (LIFO) stack of objects. The Stack interface Java should implements (without subclassing Vector). The usual push and pop operations are provided, as well as a method to peek at the top item on the stack, a method to test for whether the stack is empty. When a stack is first created, it contains no items.
